text: Scinax cretatus is a frog. It lives in Brazil. This frog lives near the edges of forests and lakes. It lives in forests not far above sea level. The adult male frog is 25.8 to 34.7 mm long from nose to rear end and the adult female frog is 29.2 to 32.5 mm long. The skin on its back is dark brown with white stripes. ==References== Category:Frogs of South America
title: Scinax cretatus
